cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper discusses defenses against adversarial examples in deep learning, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on machine learning and security, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. Additionally, since adversarial examples are often created by manipulating images, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of AI in defense mechanisms, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
